<% content_for(:title) { "Privacy Policy" } %>
<% content_for(:meta_description) { "mbuzz Privacy Policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your data. Your data belongs to you—we never sell it to third parties." } %>
<% content_for(:canonical_url) { privacy_url } %>

<%= render "layouts/nav" %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-white">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">Last updated: April 13, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TL;DR Section -->
  <section class="py-12 px-6 bg-blue-50 border-b border-blue-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">TL;DR</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>We collect only what we need to provide our service</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Your tracking data belongs to you. We never sell it. On mbuzz.co we use Google Analytics, Google Ads, and Meta for our own marketing — separate from the data we process for you</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Delete your account anytime and we delete your data (tracking data immediately, account data after 90 days)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>We use mbuzz on our own website (we eat our own cooking)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>GDPR and CCPA compliant</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-12 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-gray">
      <!-- Who We Are -->
      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        mbuzz is operated by <strong>Forebrite Pty Ltd</strong> (ABN 64 671 038 958), an Australian company.
        When we say "mbuzz," "we," "us," or "our," we mean Forebrite Pty Ltd.
      </p>

      <!-- Two Types of Data -->
      <h2>The two types of data we handle</h2>
      <p>We handle two distinct types of data:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Your account data</strong> — Information you provide when you sign up and use mbuzz
          (your email, name, company name, billing info).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Your customers' data</strong> — The events, sessions, and visitor data you collect
          through mbuzz. This is your data. We just store and process it for you.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- What We Collect -->
      <h2>What we collect from you (account holders)</h2>
      <p>When you create an mbuzz account, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email address</strong> — Required for login and communication</li>
        <li><strong>Name</strong> — So we know what to call you</li>
        <li><strong>Company name</strong> — Required to identify your account</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information</strong> — Processed securely by Stripe (we never see your full card number)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We also automatically collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Usage data</strong> — How you use mbuzz, so we can improve it</li>
        <li><strong>Technical data</strong> — Browser type, IP address for security purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- What You Collect -->
      <h2>What you collect through mbuzz (your customers' data)</h2>
      <p>
        You use mbuzz to track events on your website or app. The data you collect depends on how you
        implement mbuzz, but typically includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Page views and events</li>
        <li>Session information</li>
        <li>Visitor identifiers</li>
        <li>UTM parameters and referrer data</li>
        <li>Any custom properties you choose to track</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Important:</strong> You are the data controller for your customers' data. We are the
        data processor. You're responsible for having appropriate privacy policies and consent mechanisms
        for your own users.
      </p>

      <!-- How We Use Data -->
      <h2>How we use data</h2>
      <p><strong>Your account data:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain your mbuzz account</li>
        <li>To process payments</li>
        <li>To send important service updates (no marketing spam)</li>
        <li>To respond to support requests</li>
        <li>To improve mbuzz</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Your customers' data:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide the attribution analytics you signed up for</li>
        <li>That's it. We don't use it for anything else.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Data Storage -->
      <h2>Where we store data</h2>
      <p>
        All data is stored on servers in the <strong>United States</strong>, hosted by DigitalOcean.
        We use industry-standard security practices to protect your data.
      </p>

      <!-- Third Parties -->
      <h2>Who we share data with</h2>
      <p>We use a small number of trusted service providers:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — Payment processing</li>
        <li><strong>Postmark</strong> — Transactional emails</li>
        <li><strong>DigitalOcean</strong> — Hosting infrastructure</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We never sell your data. We never share your tracking data with advertisers. We never share
        your data across accounts or use it for other customers' benefit. When you enable data-driven
        attribution, your data is analyzed solely to improve your own attribution insights — never
        mixed with other customers' data.
      </p>

      <h3>Third parties on mbuzz.co (our marketing site only)</h3>
      <p>
        On our own marketing site (mbuzz.co), we use the following services for analytics and advertising
        measurement. These are loaded only after you give consent via the cookie banner (for visitors in
        the EEA, UK, Switzerland, and California) and do not apply to the data we process for you as a
        customer.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — Engagement analytics (page views, bounce rate, content
        performance). See
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500">Google's privacy policy</a></li>
        <li><strong>Google Ads</strong> — Conversion tracking and remarketing for ad campaign optimisation.
        <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500">Manage your Google Ads settings</a></li>
        <li><strong>Meta Pixel</strong> — Conversion tracking for Meta (Facebook/Instagram) ad campaigns.
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/adpreferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500">Manage your Meta ad preferences</a></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Data Retention -->
      <h2>How long we keep data</h2>
      <p><strong>Your customers' data (events, sessions, visitors):</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Kept as long as your account is active</li>
        <li>Deleted <strong>immediately</strong> when you delete your account</li>
        <li>You can also request deletion of specific data anytime</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Your account data:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Kept for 90 days after account deletion (in case you change your mind)</li>
        <li>Permanently deleted after 90 days</li>
        <li>Billing records kept for 7 years (legal requirement)</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Your Rights -->
      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — Request a copy of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Correct</strong> — Update inaccurate information</li>
        <li><strong>Delete</strong> — Delete your account and data</li>
        <li><strong>Export</strong> — Download your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Object</strong> — Opt out of certain processing</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights,
        <%= link_to "contact us", contact_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %>.
      </p>

      <!-- GDPR -->
      <h2>For EU residents (GDPR)</h2>
      <p>
        If you're in the European Union, you have additional rights under GDPR. We process your data
        based on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract</strong> — To provide the service you signed up for</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — To improve our service and prevent fraud</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — To comply with laws (like keeping billing records)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Our lawful basis for analytics and advertising cookies on mbuzz.co is <strong>consent</strong>
        (Art. 6(1)(a)). You can withdraw consent at any time via the cookie banner or the
        <%= link_to "Cookie Policy", cookies_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %> page.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority if you believe we've
        violated your rights.
      </p>

      <!-- CCPA -->
      <h2>For California residents (CCPA)</h2>
      <p>
        If you're in California, you have the right to know what personal information we collect,
        request deletion, and opt out of the sale of personal information.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>We do not sell personal information.</strong> We never have, and we never will. We share
        limited identifiers with Google and Meta for measurement and advertising on mbuzz.co. Under
        California law, sharing for cross-context behavioural advertising may be treated as a sale —
        you may opt out via the cookie banner or the
        <%= link_to "Cookie Policy", cookies_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %> page.
      </p>

      <!-- Cookies -->
      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        On the mbuzz dashboard (your logged-in app), we use only essential first-party cookies for
        session management and security. On mbuzz.co (our marketing site), we use Google Analytics,
        Google Ads, and Meta cookies for analytics and ad measurement — these load only after you
        give consent via the cookie banner. See our
        <%= link_to "Cookie Policy", cookies_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %>
        for a full list of cookies and how to manage your preferences.
      </p>

      <!-- Analytics -->
      <h2>Analytics on this website</h2>
      <p>
        We use mbuzz for multi-touch attribution on our own website — server-side, first-party, the
        same product we sell. For engagement analytics (bounce rate, page paths, content performance)
        we use Google Analytics 4, because mbuzz is built for attribution, not behavioural analytics.
        For ad campaign optimisation we use Google Ads and Meta Pixel. All three are gated by your
        consent and load only if you accept on the cookie banner.
      </p>

      <!-- Changes -->
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we'll notify you
        by email or through the mbuzz dashboard.
      </p>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <h2>Contact us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this privacy policy?
        <%= link_to "Get in touch", contact_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %>.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-gray-500">
        Forebrite Pty Ltd<br>
        ABN 64 671 038 958<br>
        Australia
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<%= render "layouts/footer" %>
